title: Facebook Forms New Group To Rationalize Payments Across Apps
text: Facebook Inc (NASDAQ: FB) has formed a new group, led by the co-creator of the company's Libra cryptocurrency project, David Marcus, to streamline its payments operations across app offerings, Bloomberg reported Monday.

title: Big tech is bubbling up and could spark a correction, BTIG's Julian Emanuel warns
text: BTIG's Julian Emanuel is telling clients to brace for a market pullback.

title: Facebook Stock Rated “Neutral” This Week By AI
text: Markets traded higher this week as investors continue to parse the quarterly earnings of many companies. Company-specific moves were mostly on account of its performance in the last quarter.

title: Facebook Launches New Unit To Run Its Payment Projects
text: Facebook’s new product group will be led by David Marcus and will bring together the management and strategy for all payments and financial services products and experiences across the company.

title: Facebook kicks off financial unit in another bid to capture digital payments, commerce
text: Facebook Inc. has a new payments group with a familiar face.

title: Tech Valuations Are Unsustainable: Morganlander
text: Chad Morganlander, Washington Crossing Advisors co-founder, says tech stock valuations are unsustainable.

title: Value Vs. Magic: Weighing The Big Techs
text: As a value investor, I follow growth or momentum styles, but I get the logic. But not the magical investing style that has arisen today.

title: Culture of acquisition in Big Tech is bad for competition: Columbia Law's Tim Wu
text: Tim Wu of Columbia Law School joins "Squawk Alley" to discuss whether Microsoft's potential acquisition of TikTok is bad for competition.

title: Facebook, Microsoft gripes with Apple's App Store on EU's antitrust radar
text: Facebook and Microsoft's grievances over how their gaming apps appear on Apple's App Store may feed into an EU investigation into the iPhone maker's business as EU antitrust regulators said such concerns are on their radar.

title: Former PayPal exec Stephane Kasriel will head Facebook Pay, its Venmo-like service, backed by new team
text: The company launched Facebook Pay, which allows users to send money over its family of apps, on Facebook proper and Facebook Messenger last November.

title: US Tech Giants Push Back Against India's Forced Data-Sharing Plan: Report
text: A group representing the United States technology giants is pushing back against India’s plans to regulate “non-personal” data, Reuters reported Sunday.
